            . I am the prosecutor's grandfather. On the 7th of June, the prisoner came and asked for ten sovereigns and a five pound note, for my son, which I gave him - he never returned.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was rather in liquor at the time, and as I returned, met a friend, drank with him, and lost the 5 l. note somehow. A young man met me, and said I had better go and lay down with him, which I did, and he robbed me of the ten sovereigns.</p>
